6.2.5

Given sample space \(\{a, b, c, d\}\) and events \(A = \{a, b\}\), \(B = \{a, c\}\). If \(A\) and \(B\) are independent, prove that \(P (a)P (d) = P (b)P (c)\).



Proof

\((P_a+P_b)(P_a+P_c)=P_a\)

\(P_a^2+P_a(P_b+P_c)+P_bP_c=P_a\)

\(P_a^2+P_bP_c=P_a(1-P_b-P_c)\)

\(P_a^2+P_bP_c=P_a(P_a+P_d)\)

\(P_bP_c=P_aP_d\)
